In [38]:
def waveplot(y):
    print(f'y shape {y.shape}')
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
    librosa.display.waveshow(y)
    plt.ylabel('amplitude')
    plt.xlabel('time')
    plt.show()
    

def ff_spectogram(y):
    ft = np.abs(librosa.stft(y))
    print(f'ft shape {ft.shape}')
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
    plt.plot(ft)
    plt.ylabel('amplitude')
    plt.xlabel('frequency')
    plt.show()
    

def timestamps_spectogram(y, sr):
    S = librosa.feature.melspectrogram(y=y, sr=sr)
    print(f'Spectogram shape: {S.shape}')
    S_dB = librosa.power_to_db(S, ref=np.max)
    plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))
    img = librosa.display.specshow(S_dB, x_axis='time',
                                   y_axis='mel', sr=sr,
                                   fmax=8000)
    plt.show()


def analyse_audio(category):
    root = 'TESS\TESS Toronto emotional speech set data'
    file = os.listdir(f'{root}/{category}')[0]
    print(category, ':')
    y, sr = librosa.load(f'{root}/{category}/{file}')
    waveplot(y)
    ff_spectogram(y)
    timestamps_spectogram(y, sr)
    display(Audio(y, rate=sr))

linear_chirp = librosa.chirp(fmin=110, fmax=110*64 , sr=22050, length=22050, linear=False)
librosa.display.waveshow(linear_chirp[:50])
plt.show()
librosa.display.waveshow(linear_chirp[:7000])
plt.show()
display(Audio(linear_chirp, rate=22050))
S_linear = np.abs(librosa.stft(y=linear_chirp))
librosa.display.specshow(librosa.amplitude_to_db(S_linear, ref=np.max),
                         x_axis='time', y_axis='linear')
